.TH "git-crawler" "1" "July 14, 2014" " 0.1.3" "Networking Tools"
.SH "NAME"
git-crawler \(em Git Email Crawler, and Information Disclosure Tool
.SH "MODES"
.IP "\fB""Remote Repo"" mode:\fP"
Find email leaks within a remote repo not available locally (works great both with public and private repos).
.IP "\fB""Local Repo"" mode:\fP"
Find email leaks within a local repo downloaded at your workstation.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB-r\fP \fISTRING\fP, \fB--remote=\fP\fISTRING\fP"
Set the remote git repo to be audited (.git url)
.IP "\fB-l\fP \fISTRING\fP, \fB--local=\fP\fISTRING\fP"
Set the local git repo to be audited (path)
.br
.IP "\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP"
Show this help.


.SH "USE EXAMPLE"
.PP
.IP "$ python git-crawler.py -r https://github.com/eif0/xibalba.git"
Audit eif0/xibalba's repo (remotely from GitHub) and search for leaked emails.

.IP "$ python git-crawler.py -l /path/to/MyClonedProject"
Audit MyClonedProject's repo (stored locally) and search for leaked emails.

.IP "$ python git-crawler.py --help"
Show this help.

